org.isda.cdm

Class Contract

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rosetta.model.lib.RosettaModelObject
      • org.isda.cdm.Contract
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.rosetta.model.lib.RosettaKey

    @RosettaClass
public class Contract
extends com.rosetta.model.lib.RosettaModelObject
implements com.rosetta.model.lib.RosettaKey
    A class to specify a contract object, which can be invoked either within the context of an event, or independently from it. It corresponds to the FpML Trade, although restricted to execution and post-execution contexts. Attributes also applicable to pre-execution (a.k.a. pre-trade view in FpML) contexts have been positioned as part of the ContractualProduct class.

      • getParty

        @RosettaSynonym(value="party",
                source="FpML")
public final List<Party> getParty()
        The parties to the contract. The cardinality is optional to address the case where the contract object is part of an event record, in which case the party is specified as part of that object. In that respect, the CDM approach is distinct from FpML, where party information is specified as part of a wrapper alongside the trade object.

      • getTradeDate

        public final DateInstances getTradeDate()
        The trade date. This is the date on which the trade was originally executed. The trade date is specified through the DateInstances class so that in the case of a novation the novated part of the trade be reported (by both the remaining party and the transferee) using the date on which the novation was agreed on. The remaining part of a trade is to be reported (by both the transferor and the remaining party) using a trade date corresponding to the original execution date.
